Changamwe MP aspirant Peterson Mitau has expressed confidence he will defeat incumbent Omar Mwinyi.Mitau is an independent candidate.He said he will also beat Jubilee Party candidate Abdi Daib hands down.This is Mitau&rsquo;s third attempt in the Changamwe MP race, after losing in 2007 and 2013.The businessman launched his campaigns on Sunday.&ldquo;This time round it will not be business as usual. I want to ask my competitors in NASA and Jubilee to prepare themselves for a huge defeat. I will emerge victorious on August 8,&rdquo; Mitau said.